          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-05-06T20:10:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>21st Century Investment Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) make permanent the tax credit for increasing research activities; (2) allow an increased 25% tax credit rate for research expenses incurred in the United States; and (3) increase to 15%, through 2024, the tax deduction for income attributable to domestic manufacturing production activities for which substantially all of the research and development occurred in the United States. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-04-16T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
